# task #134 (Reconnect): Reconnect is an explicit RESTART, not a reuse — a live daemon is
# torn down first (state saved, login untouched) and a fresh one spawned; exactly one
# daemon exists afterwards (never the "address already in use" pile-up).
desc tailscale-lib: Reconnect restarts a LIVE daemon (kill old, fresh spawn, one daemon)
invoke tslib
tsdaemon slow:10
sdfile+ .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.state
tsdrv up
tsdrv reconnect
tsdrv count
expect_exit 0
expect_trace TSDRV up rc=0
expect_trace TSDRV reconnect rc=0 tok=connected:100.64.0.9
expect_trace TSDRV daemons=1
expect_file_has .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.log ts reconnect ---
expect_file_has .userdata/tg5040/tailscale/tailscaled.log reconnect: Running again
